About
Town Square is a shopping, dining and entertainment center on Las Vegas Boulevard at the junction of I-15 and the 215 Beltway. The 93-acre, open-air center features 24 buildings detailing a collage of Old World and contemporary architectural styles.

puggirlthurman
Milwaukee, WI6 contributions
Great place to kill time
Nov 2022
I flew into Vegas alone until my family were to come the next day. I had an airbnb and could not check in until later in the evening. I did some research and came upon this mall. I had been to Vegas before. But. This really interested me. And boy was I glad to get there. I took the deuce (the bus as it is called in Vegas). And was very surprised. If you look over. You can still see the hotels in the background of Vegas. The palm trees were so pretty. And lots of people and families were out and about. My first stop was to get lunch. I went to a place called 2 hands. A Korean corn dog stand. I loved it!. I also had a boba tea at 'Chewy Boba Company". There was a line so I knew this place was going to be good. The weather was amazing in Vegas for a November. This place is hug. I went shopping to many of the stores I was familiar with in my home state. And many stores I never heard of. The whole place had a great vibe. I was very happy I was there to experience an amazing place. You will do a lot of walking and you have to watch out for the cars. Going back to catch the deuce . There is a long walk back to the bus stop. Things appear close but. Are far away. So comfortable walking shoes are a must. I even interacted with the locals to get a take on what they like to eat and where to go. The locals are more than happy to tell you. On my next trip to Vegas. I will definitely be back here.
Written December 5, 2022

Written October 2, 2016
arsherman3
Brentwood, California
35 contributions
Planet Hollywood is not part of Town Square. Town Square is an outdoor mixed use shopping center with dinning, bars and a movie theater as well as office on the upper floors. I'd ask the valet or front desk if a shuttle gets you close to Planet Hollywood or take a cab/uber/lyft. Las Vegas has tons of visitors during the slow times and you don't want to end up far away when you have a show or reservation to make. Depending on the hotel you are staying at it may just be easier, and faster, to walk. I hope this helps. Enjoy Las Vegas its a great town!
